
Stateless Widget: The widgets whose state can not be altered once they are built
 are called stateless widgets.

 A stateful widget is dynamic: for example, it can change its appearance in response to
  events triggered by user interactions or when it receives data.
  Checkbox , Radio , Slider , InkWell , Form , and TextField are examples of stateful widgets.

  condition ? exp1 : exp2
  If condition is true, evaluate exp1 else exp2

  exp1 ?? exp2
  if exp1 =! null, return its value else evaluate and return the value of exp2